table.name: CONFIG_ENVIRONMENT_SERVERS
table.Comment: each environment will be hosted on 1 or more servers each server will cater to 0 or more environments

table.name: CONFIG_OPERATING_SYSTEMS
table.Comment: Sever will be either hosted on Windows or Linux OS

table.name: CONFIG_SERVER_ROLES
table.Comment: Server Roles like ALLINONE_SERVER, DEDICATED_DATABASE_SERVER, DEDICATED_APP_SERVER etc

table.name: CONFIG_SERVER_TYPES
table.Comment: server type like AppServer, Dispatch server, Job Server, DB Server

column.name: CP_ID
column.Comment: Single unique ID for every Client_project_id + sub_project_id in the format <client_id>-<client_sub_project_id> e.g. 103-01

column.name: CP_SUB_PROJECT_ID
column.Comment: sub project id is assigned if a client has multiple division and each division has its own set of environments

column.name: CP_CLIENT_NAME
column.Comment: Name of Client as per contract

column.name: CP_IS_DELETED
column.Comment: Status of Client Project 0 - Active, 1- Inactive

column.name: DB_SCHEMA_ENV_UUID
column.Comment: Environment Id. For Values check CONFIG_ENVIRONMENTS table

column.name: DB_SCHEMA_SCHEMA_TYPE_ID
column.Comment: SPM or report schema. For all values refer CONFIG_SCHEMA_TYPES tables

column.name: DB_SCHEMA_DATAFILE_PATH
column.Comment: path where datafiles for this schema are stored

column.name: DATA_CENTER_OCM_URL
column.Comment: OCM URL for Data Center. We have one OCM per data center

column.name: DATA_CENTER_OCM_URL
column.Comment: OCM URL for Data Center. We have one OCM per data center

column.name: ENV_UUID
column.Comment: Environment unique identifier across data centers. Will be a alpha numeric string and will be used to identify environments in Data Warehouse

column.name: ENV_ID
column.Comment: Unique within a data center. Kept for backward compatibility

column.name: ENV_NAME
column.Comment: Environment name, unique within a data center

column.name: ENV_DATA_CENTER_ID
column.Comment: Data Center - TCS or AWS. For values refer CONFIG_DATA_CENTERS table

column.name: ENV_ENV_TYPE_ID
column.Comment: e.g. Production or sandbox. For all value refer CONFIG_ENVIRONMENT_TYPES table

column.name: ENV_CP_ID
column.Comment: Client Project Psuedo Id. For values refer CONFIG_CLIENT_PROJECTS table

column.name: ENV_FARM_ID
column.Comment: Farm Id. For farm name refer to CONFIG_FARMS table

column.name: ENV_START_DATE
column.Comment: Date when the environment was first provisioned

column.name: ENV_END_DATE
column.Comment: Date when the environment was decommissioned

column.name: STATUS
column.Comment: Y is Active and N is Inactive

column.name: ENV_VERSION
column.Comment: Version on which the environment exists

column.name: ENV_SERVER_OPERATING_SYSTEM_ID
column.Comment: Windows or Linus. All values can be found in CONFIG_OPERATING_SYSTEMS table

column.name: ENV_SERVER_SERVER_TYPE_ID
column.Comment: Server type like app server or Database server. for all types refer CONFIG_SERVER_TYPES

column.name: ENV_SERVER_SERVER_ROLE_ID
column.Comment: Server Role like Shared or dedicated. For all roles refer CONFIG_SERVER_ROLES table

column.name: ENV_SERVER_START_DATE
column.Comment: when was server first provisioned/allocated to environment

column.name: STATUS
column.Comment: Y is Active and N is Inactive

column.name: FARM_DATA_CENTER_ID
column.Comment: FARM Id will be unique within a data center

column.name: CMA_TO_FLAG
column.Comment: DECIDE WHOM TO SEND MAIL (TO) 1: DISTRIBUTION LIST 2: RECIPIENT 3: BOTH DISTRIBUTION LIST AND RECIPIENTS

column.name: CMA_CC_FLAG
column.Comment: DECIDE WHOM TO SEND MAIL (CC) 1: DISTRIBUTION LIST 2: RECIPIENT 3: BOTH DISTRIBUTION LIST AND RECIPIENTS

column.name: CMA_BCC_FLAG
column.Comment: DECIDE WHOM TO SEND MAIL (BCC) 1: DISTRIBUTION LIST 2: RECIPIENT 3: BOTH DISTRIBUTION LIST AND RECIPIENTS

column.name: CMA_NOTIFY_ITERATION_NUMBER
column.Comment: Iteration Number on/after which alert should be sent

column.name: CMV_SCHEDULED_REFRESH_DAY
column.Comment: Materialized view scheduled refresh day For monthly refresh- 01-31(Nth Day of the month),For weekly refresh - 0-7(Nth Day of the week, e.g 1-Sun, 2-Mon..), For Daily refresh - 0

column.name: CMV_ACTUAL_REFRESH_DATE
column.Comment: Date on which mview get refreshed

column.name: CMV_REFRESH_STATUS
column.Comment: Materialized view Refresh status(N-Not refreshed, B-refresh broken, F-refresh failed after tryout days, Y-sucessfully refreshed)

column.name: CMV_LINKED_METRIC_ID
column.Comment: Materialized view linked to the metric id

column.name: CMV_SCHEDULED_REFRESH_DAY
column.Comment: Materialized view scheduled refresh day For monthly refresh- 01-31(Nth Day of the month),For weekly refresh - 0-7(Nth Day of the week, e.g 1-Sun, 2-Mon..), For Daily refresh - 0

column.name: CMV_ACTUAL_REFRESH_DATE
column.Comment: Date on which mview get refreshed

column.name: CMV_REFRESH_STATUS
column.Comment: Materialized view Refresh status(N-Not refreshed, B-refresh broken, F-refresh failed after tryout days, Y-sucessfully refreshed)

column.name: CMV_LINKED_METRIC_ID
column.Comment: Materialized view linked to the metric id

column.name: METRIC_NAME
column.Comment: Metric Identifier. All Input files/metrics should come with this identifier

column.name: METRIC_SOURCE_ID
column.Comment: Source of metric - application metric/PHS/operating system etc. Refers to source_Id from Config_Sources

column.name: METRIC_TABLE_NAME
column.Comment: Physical table name for that metric

column.name: METRIC_INPUT_FILE_PATH
column.Comment: Relative path to telemetry warehouse root folder. Path for the root folder can be found in CONFIG_PROPERTIES table

column.name: METRIC_EXT_FILE_NAME_FORMAT
column.Comment: We will using external files to load data to Warehouse. Specify file format for external table for this metric

column.name: METRIC_EXTERNAL_TABLE_NAME
column.Comment: External Table name for the metric

column.name: METRIC_DEFAULT_DIRECTORY_NAME
column.Comment: External Table's default Dierctory name for the metric

column.name: METRIC_FREQUENCY
column.Comment: Frequency for collecting metric data, 0-All days, 1- every Sunday, 2- every Monday, 3- every Tuesday , 4- every Wednesday, 5- every Thursday, 6- every Friday, 7-every Saturday

column.name: METRIC_A_COLUMN_NAME
column.Comment: Physical Column name in metric table within database

column.name: METRIC_A_MAPPED_NAME
column.Comment: Name of column header in source file/table

column.name: METRIC_A_ORDER
column.Comment: Order of columns in destination table and source file

column.name: OPERATING_SYSTEM_NAME
column.Comment: name of operating system like Linux or windows

column.name: SCHEMA_TYPE_VALUE
column.Comment: Values can be SPM, Logi, Report schema etc

column.name: SERVER_ROLE_NAME
column.Comment: Example coule be 1 ALLINONE_SERVER, 2 DEDICATED_DATABASE_SERVER 3 DEDICATED_APP_SERVER 4 DEDICATED_JOB_SERVER 5 DEDICATED_FILE_SERVER 6 SHARED_WEB_SERVER 7 DEDICATED_LOGIN_SERVER 10 SHARED_LOGIN_SERVER 11 APP/JOB_SERVER 12 SHARED_REPOSITORY 13 SHARED_VIEWER 14 SHARED_IMPL_SERVER 15 SHARED_DB_SERVER 16 DEDICATED_WEB_SERVER

column.name: SERVER_TYPE_VALUE
column.Comment: Example would be App/Glassfish Server,Dispatcher/DAS server,Job Server,DB Server,Load Balancer,OCM,NGINX,Login Server,SSO Server,Logi Server,Project Root Server.Exchange Server

column.name: SOURCE_VALUE
column.Comment: Source of metric - application metric/PHS/operating system etc

column.name: TMAL_MAIL_BCC
column.Comment: Comma Seperated Email ID/s (Blind Carbon Copy)

column.name: TMAL_MAIL_SENT
column.Comment: Mail Sent Status Y:Sent N:Not Sent

column.name: TMAIL_ERROR_EVENT_DATE
column.Comment: Error event date from telemetry error logs table
